From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 23:02:26 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: add hard compact tests (lambda capture, deep
 nesting)

Two more verified hard-scenario tests: a lambda capturing a hot/cold-reordered compact struct by reference and reading several reordered members in constexpr; and four levels of nested compact structs where writing/taking-address of the deepest leaf must compose offsets through every reordered subobject. Both validated against the real binary. No compiler change.



diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-deeply-nested-reordered-access.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-deeply-nested-reordered-access.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..978562970
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-deeply-nested-reordered-access.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,20 @@
+// HARD: four levels of nested compact structs, each independently reordered.
+// Writing through and taking the address of the deepest leaf must compute the
+// offset correctly, composed through every reordered subobject at every level.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -verify %s
+// expected-no-diagnostics
+
+compact struct L4 { char pad; int leaf; };
+compact struct L3 { char pad; L4 d; };
+compact struct L2 { char pad; L3 c; };
+compact struct L1 { char pad; L2 b; };
+
+constexpr int deep() {
+  L1 a{};
+  a.b.c.d.leaf = 42;      // offset composes through 4 reordered levels
+  int *p = &a.b.c.d.leaf; // address through the chain
+  return *p;
+}
+
+static_assert(deep() == 42, "deep nested reordered access is offset-correct");
diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-lambda-over-reordered-members.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-lambda-over-reordered-members.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..7d5168af3
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-lambda-over-reordered-members.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@
+// HARD: a lambda captures a compact (hot/cold-reordered) struct by reference and
+// touches several of its reordered members inside a constexpr evaluation. Member
+// access by name must resolve to the correct field regardless of physical order,
+// and the closure must observe one consistent layout.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -verify %s
+// expected-no-diagnostics
+
+compact struct V3 { hot double x; cold char tag; double y; double z; };
+
+constexpr double sum() {
+  V3 v{};
+  v.x = 1;
+  v.y = 2;
+  v.z = 3;
+  v.tag = 'a';
+  auto f = [&] { return v.x + v.y + v.z; }; // touches reordered members
+  return f();
+}
+
+static_assert(sum() == 6.0, "lambda reads the right reordered fields");
